```json
{
  "application": "SLURM",
  "details": {
    "nodes": 1,
    "partition": "gpu",
    "gpus": 1,
    "cores": 12,
    "gpu_per_task": 1,
    "constraint": "a100",
    "time": "1:00:00",
    "memory": "32G",
    "job_name": "resnorm",
    "output": "./out/resnet/out.%j.%a.%N.out",
    "error": "./err/resnet/err.%j.%a.%N.err",
    "script": "run_code_resnet.sh"
  }
}
```

This script is using the **SLURM** workload manager to run a job. It's requesting 1 node with 1 GPU, 12 cores, and a specific constraint ("a100"). It's also setting a time limit of 1 hour, a memory limit of 32GB, and giving the job a name "resnorm". 

The script uses a parameter file and runs an external script called "run_code_resnet.sh" with the parameters from the file.
